metadata.name: de|growth:generations #46
metadata.description:
Materials tend to take particular forms due to their physical properties, technological necessities or natural limitations. However, what rules should a simulated environment follow when no physical constraints are inherent to the digital environment?

This project continues the exploration of shaping digital matter that I began on hicetnunc in 2021. Each token creates an image of a unique sculpture generated with a custom growth/degrowth algorithm. The image is rendered with a tailored raytracing script.

---
Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones for the 800x800px image.

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the resolution from preview quality to a print of approx. 30x30cm. There may be minor differences in tone or contrast for different resolutions.

In live mode:
Click PNG to save the rendered image.
Click STL to download the digital model to view on your computer or 3d print at home [experimental]

metadata.name: In the Edge #316
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.

metadata.name: Love & Wild #59
metadata.description:
We often use flowers to express untold feelings towards our loved ones and most precious people in our life. But love as flowers can go wild & in unpredictable directions.

Love & Wild code come to life few weeks ago when I was alone drinking coffee at local bar, started messing with vertex Quadratic bezier and first petal appeared on screen. After few Loved flowers, the Wild ones start to emerge. Those with sharp spines that are beautiful in it’s own way but can also, like Love, inflict pain. As I was on vacation during finalising this work the colors and flavours of the Mediterranean inspired me.
But except some Wild palettes too.

Thank You

‘s’ for save canvas.
‘2’ for HD png.
‘4’ for 4000x4000px png.
‘8’ for 8000x8000px png.

Created with wild love for p5js and generative art :)
@Qotonana
July, 2022.

metadata.name: The Nightmare Factory (Pt.II) #7
metadata.description:
You can’t tell the mysterious sender’s true intentions. Why put these images up behind a crypto paywall? Why this site? 

It appears to be a collection of scratchy photos taken of polaroids. Why is the husband in possession of these photos? How involved is he with this horrific project?

While the images are shocking, you’re captivated by the faded notes you find written on the polaroids. Out of order, it’s hard to tell what’s going on without reading more, and you find yourself paying up again and again to learn the truth.

There seems to be two distinct sets of handwriting...

When were these taken?

What is really going on at this “Nightmare Factory?”

Where is this lab located? 

Some of these mysteries might be solved, while others may only be found by deeper discoveries, over time. 

---------
An multi-platform, multimedia project, Part I can be found on at https://typed.art/@DarkWheelNFT

This is Part II. 

Minters of this project get a 5% royalty, because you make this project as much as I do.

1% of royalty goes to Pure Spider for his template, which this is built on.

There are:
6 backgrounds,
5 cells,
8 color gels,
7 photo frames,
5 color overlays,
10 textures.

Most importantly there are:
21 different images for the Subjects, all of the same rarity
22 different traits for the text, all of the same rarity. 

Part III is pending, and will require a motivated collector or team thereof. 


The first collector to own all 21 different subjects in one wallet (and contacts me on twitter: @darkwheelNFT) will trigger the minting of a 1/1 airdrop “Subject 13 - Day 26,” and a 1/13 piece on Objkt titled “The Cleaner’s Last Message,” and the wallet of your choosing will be listed for 5% royalties for both pieces.

The first collector to own all 22 different text traits in one wallet (and contacts me on twitter: @darkwheelNFT) will trigger the minting of a 1/1 airdrop “The Anti-Doctor,” and a 1/13 piece on Objkt titled “Log: 19830221 - On Subject 13,” and the wallet of your choosing will be listed for 5% royalties for both pieces.


If you are seeking to collect either of the 1/1 airdrops, please make sure no one else has beat you to the punch.

metadata.name: Études #184
metadata.description:
- Click to start the sound - 

‘Études’ is a series of generative notation accompanied with sound.

‘Études’ is the first series of the ‘Notations’ collection. ‘Notations’ will explore various notation techniques around the world and will use different sonification techniques and generative music algorithms.

In this series, a sonification process has been used to generate sound.

Some articulations or accidentals intentionally exist due to aesthetic preferences. For example there are some musically meaningless things like vibrato on a piano or a coda sign on a motif. And some notes will play the same pitch (even if they appear apart from one another) depending on the chosen scale.

Sonification tends to work better after 2nd (or even 3rd) play. Some minor audio bugs might occur. 

There is a major but a rare bug which we intentionally kept in; it plays a generative piece from indicated pitches rather than just playing the motif only once.

There is a rare possibility that ‘Études’ can generate an ‘electronic’ result which plays with a FM synth instead of piano.

Probabilities;

- 12 root notes

 - 12 different scales

- Dynamics; pp,p,mp,mf,f,ff or none

- Dynamic changes; crescendo and diminuendo or none

- 4 different noteheads

- Several accidentals and articulations

- Vibrato might occur on some outputs

- 3 font styles

- 4 background textures


Made with p5.js
Ilgın İçözü, March 2022
@distcollective
